Normies really love "chores humor", like a couple is making out and suddenly the girl slips a vacuum cleaner into the man's hand to clean the room or she calls him erotically over to the kitchen and there are dirty dishes there in the sink. It's a central part of their culture.

The only non-technological (thus non-quantitative) solution to the chores issue is Miyazaki's pseudo-Buddhist idea of seeing them as an opportunity to practice "mindfulness" or romanticizing them a bit. This is also why everyone should see all Ghibli films as a child (ideally)...
